## Platform Reference Docs

Before writing code for any managed platform, check these constraint docs (bundled with Executive OS plugin):

| Platform | Reference | Key Constraints |
|----------|-----------|-----------------|
| n8n Cloud | `~/Projects/executive-os-plugin/references/platform-references/n8n-cloud.md` | 60s Code node timeout, no fetch(), use this.helpers.httpRequest() |
| GCP Cloud Run | `~/Projects/executive-os-plugin/references/platform-references/gcp-cloud-run.md` | 900s timeout, 2Gi memory, Secret Manager for credentials |
| Google APIs | `~/Projects/executive-os-plugin/references/platform-references/google-apis.md` | Use batchGet not sequential, supportsAllDrives=True for Shared Drives |
| HubSpot API | `~/Projects/executive-os-plugin/references/platform-references/hubspot-api.md` | 100 req/10s rate limit, dedup on email only, pipeline/field IDs |
| HubSpot Conventions | `~/Projects/executive-os-plugin/references/platform-references/hubspot-conventions.md` | Em-dash naming prefix, static list IDs, deal source enums |
| Apollo API | `~/Projects/executive-os-plugin/references/platform-references/apollo-api.md` | User-Agent + Cache-Control headers REQUIRED on PUT/POST |
| Lovable | `~/Projects/executive-os-plugin/references/platform-references/lovable.md` | Prompt by component not page, 10K char knowledge limits, Supabase backend, RLS before production |

> If no reference doc exists for a platform you're working with, research constraints FIRST and create the doc in `~/Projects/executive-os-plugin/references/platform-references/`.

