## Google Workspace (gws CLI)

All Google Workspace services (Gmail, Calendar, Drive, Chat, Docs, Sheets, Slides, People) are accessed via the `gws` CLI using the Bash tool — **not** via an MCP server. Usage pattern:

```bash
gws <service> <resource> <method> --params '{"key": "value"}'
```

Each team member authenticates with their own nuDesk Google account. Run `gws auth setup` to configure. See `~/Projects/executive-os-plugin/references/mcp-setup/gws-cli-setup.md` for full setup guide.

